<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Cottingley_Fairies_1.jpg" class="image" title="Frances Griffiths with the alleged fairies, taken by Elsie Wright in July 1917. One of the five photographs."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/71/Cottingley_Fairies_1.jpg/250px-Cottingley_Fairies_1.jpg" width="250" height="200" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Cottingley_Fairies_1.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Frances Griffiths with the alleged fairies, taken by Elsie Wright in July 1917. One of the five photographs.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Cottingley Fairies</b> are a series of five photographs taken by Elsie Wright and Frances Griffiths, two young <a href="/wiki/Cousins" title="Cousins">cousins</a> living in <a href="/wiki/Cottingley,_Bradford" title="Cottingley, Bradford">Cottingley</a>, near <a href="/wiki/Bradford" title="Bradford">Bradford</a> in <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>, depicting the two in various activities with supposed <a href="/wiki/Fairies" title="Fairies">fairies</a>. In 1917, when the first two photos were taken, Elsie was 16 years old and Frances was 10. In 1981 the two women admitted to faking all but one of the photographs, but insisted that they really had seen fairies.</p>
