<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Cottingley_Fairies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i>The Coming of the Fairies</i> by Arthur Conan Doyle, Hodder &amp; Stoughton, hardback, 1922.</li>
<li><i>The Unexplained, Mysteries of Mind, Space &amp; Time</i>. Edited by Brian Innes and Peter Brookesmith, a weekly part work published by Orbis Publishing Ltd. Republished as <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0874755751" class="internal">ISBN 0-87475-575-1</a>. The Cottingley articles occur in volume 5, pp. 584 - 601.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFRandi1982"><a href="/wiki/James_Randi" title="James Randi">Randi, James</a> (1982), <i><a href="/wiki/Flim-Flam!" title="Flim-Flam!" class="mw-redirect">Flim-Flam!</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Prometheus_Books" title="Prometheus Books">Prometheus Books</a>, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0879751983" class="internal">ISBN 0-87975-198-3</a></cite></li>
</ul>
